OL,3,CYoga teacher aims to raise awareness
OL,4,Cof origins and meaning of the practice
OL,6,FSome examples of yoga that are not the
OL,7,Fphysical poses we know today, include
OL,8,Fmediation, breath-work and practising
OL,9,Fthe philosophy of morals and ethics.
OL,11,FChandi Nijhawan said: "Yoga basically
OL,12,F- what it's not is a physical fitness
OL,13,Fclass, it's an entire life system.
OL,15,F"If you imagine yoga as a wheel, and
OL,16,Fin the centre of the wheel is
OL,17,Fconnection to self, and you reach yoga
OL,18,Ffrom many different paths.
